thread.title: Packers got bailed out of an Aaron Rodgers interception with a pass interference call
thread.title_full: Packers got bailed out of an Aaron Rodgers interception with a pass interference call

author: Harry Lyles Jr.
title: Packers got bailed out of an Aaron Rodgers interception with a pass interference call
text:
This was big.
There have been questions regarding the officiating in the NFC Divisional Round game between the Packers and Cowboys. That was the case on this particular play.
Aaron Rodgers wound up, and heaved one to Ty Montgomery as he was being hit. The Cowboys were called for a pass interference, when it appears it should have been a holding.
Because pass interference was called, the Packers got the first down at the 35-yard line.
The Packers were held to a field goal by the Cowboys, but it sure appeared that play was going to be the dagger in the hearts of Dallas.
